Code review complete. I've identified **4 bugs** in `middleware/wrap_writer.go` and saved the detailed report to `/sessions/quirky-practical-cerf/mnt/QPB/benchmarks/run_001/chi/haiku/code_reviews/CHI-16_review.md`.

## Summary of Findings:

| Line | Type | Severity | Issue |
|------|------|----------|-------|
| 118 | BUG | High | `flushWriter.Flush()` sets `wroteHeader=true` without calling `maybeWriteHeader()`, causing `Status()` to return 0 instead of 200 |
| 135 | BUG | High | `httpFancyWriter.Flush()` has same bug as line 118 |
| 153 | BUG | High | `ReadFrom()` double-counts bytes when tee writer is active (increments via `Write()` calls, then again manually) |
| 177 | BUG | High | `http2FancyWriter.Flush()` has same bug as line 118 |

All findings include:
